answers.body_markdown:
Unfortunately*, you can&#39;t use `String.replaceAll` for this. That&#39;s because `toUpperCase()` is called on `&quot;$1&quot;`, not each actual match.

You can use `Matcher.replaceAll(Function&lt;MatchResult, String&gt;)` for this (with thanks to Jon Skeet):
```java
// Pattern is immutable, so creating shared instances is good practice
private static final Pattern STRING_TRANSFORM_PATTERN = Pattern.compile(&quot;([a-z])\\1&quot;);

public static String stringTransform(String str) {
    return STRING_TRANSFORM_PATTERN
            .matcher(str)
            .replaceAll(match -&gt; &quot;Double&quot; + match.group(1).toUpperCase());
}
```

Use the _[Pattern](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/api/java.base/java/util/regex/Pattern.html)_ and _[Matcher](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/api/java.base/java/util/regex/Matcher.html)_ class, utilizing the _[replaceAll](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/api/java.base/java/util/regex/Matcher.html#replaceAll(java.util.function.Function))_ method.

```java
Pattern p = Pattern.compile(&quot;([a-z])\\1&quot;);
Matcher m = p.matcher(str);
return m.replaceAll(x -&gt; &quot;Double&quot; + m.group(1).toUpperCase());
```

Or, the _[appendReplacement](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/api/java.base/java/util/regex/Matcher.html#appendReplacement(java.lang.StringBuilder,java.lang.String))_ and _[appendTail](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/api/java.base/java/util/regex/Matcher.html#appendReplacement(java.lang.StringBuilder,java.lang.String))_ methods.

```java
Pattern p = Pattern.compile(&quot;([a-z])\\1&quot;);
Matcher m = p.matcher(str);
StringBuilder s = new StringBuilder();
while (m.find())
    m.appendReplacement(s, &quot;Double&quot; + m.group(1).toUpperCase());
m.appendTail(s);
return s.toString();
```

Alternately, use a _loop_ to find each occurrence of _&quot;Double&quot;_, and uppercase the succeeding character.

```java
str = str.replaceAll(&quot;([a-z])\\1&quot;,&quot;Double$1&quot;);
StringBuilder s = new StringBuilder(str);
int o = -1;
while ((o = s.indexOf(&quot;Double&quot;, o + 1)) != -1)
    s.setCharAt(o + 6, Character.toUpperCase(s.charAt(o + 6)));
return s.toString();
```

Or, a less practical approach would be to try each _double a &amp;ndash; z_.

```java
for (char c = &#39;a&#39;; c &lt;= &#39;z&#39;; c++)
    str = str.replaceAll(c + &quot;&quot; + c, &quot;Double&quot; + Character.toUpperCase(c));
return str;
```

